         <abstract>
            <p>Chebyshev series approximations are given for the complete Bose-Einstein functions of orders 1 to 10. This paper also gives an exhaustive presentation of the relation of this function to other functions, with the emphasis that some Fermi-Dirac functions and polylogarithms are readily computable from the given approximations. The coefficients are given in 21 significant figures and the maximal relative error for function representation ranges from 2 × 10&lt;sup&gt;-20&lt;/sup&gt; to 3 × 10&lt;sup&gt;-19&lt;/sup&gt;. These expansions are fast convergent; for example, typically six terms gives an accuracy of 10&lt;sup&gt;-8&lt;/sup&gt;.</p>
          </abstract>
